algorithm: The new algorithm calculates the score for each bin by dividing the product of the logarithm of the item size and the reciprocal of the sum of the rest capacities of all bins by the sum of the rest capacities of all bins plus the item size raised to the power of a constant value.
code:
import numpy as np

def score(item: int, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    sum_rest_capacity = np.sum(bins)
    log_item_size = np.log(item)
    constant_value = 2    # Change the constant value as desired
    scores = (log_item_size / sum_rest_capacity) / (sum_rest_capacity + item)**constant_value
    return scores
